On top of that, they have to learn U.S. History.  I think it's a pretty motivational guide for Hispanics to learn basic English, if it's U.S. Citizenship they want.<br>
<br>
It's not the sort of study guide you get at school where they tell you what's gonna exactly be on the test.  It's an overview of the process and what the test will include (as far as oral exams, multiple choice questions, what forms to bring, what happens after the interview and test, etc. etc.).<br>
